# Aipify Development Rule — Cursor Optimization

## Purpose

Cursor should focus only on implementing the **current phase**.

## Rules

1. Do **NOT** revisit previous phases.
2. Do **NOT** validate previous phases.
3. Do **NOT** regenerate earlier content.
4. Do **NOT** re-read historical phase documents.
5. Assume all previously approved phases are complete and implemented correctly.
6. Focus exclusively on the functionality introduced by the **current phase**.
7. Build only what is described in the active phase document.
8. Preserve existing architecture unless the current phase explicitly requires modification.
9. Avoid introducing unnecessary dependencies on previous phases.
10. Keep implementation simple, focused, and production-ready.

## Phase document structure

```
AIPIFY – PHASE XXX
TITLE: [Phase Title]
PURPOSE: A short explanation of what this phase introduces.
OBJECTIVES: • Objective 1 • Objective 2 …
REQUIREMENTS: • Requirement 1 • Requirement 2 …
COMPONENTS: • Component 1 • Component 2 …
SECURITY REQUIREMENTS: GitHub-style 2FA, enterprise permissions, audit logging remain active.
AIPIFY PRINCIPLES: People First. Technology Second. Self Love. Wisdom before speed. Companionship before replacement. Growth through support. Stewardship through responsibility.
END OF PHASE.
```

## Important

- Do not search for previous phases.
- Do not attempt to understand the entire Aipify ecosystem before implementing the current phase.
- Assume all previous work is approved.
- Implement only the **delta** introduced in the current document.
- Forward momentum is more important than historical reconstruction.

**Build the feature. Ship the feature. Continue the evolution.**
